# Design System

All CSS values must come from `site/design-system/tokens.css`. No hardcoded px, rem, hex, rgb, or color names elsewhere.

## Token files

- `tokens.css` — colors (`--color-*`, `--stage-*`), spacing (`--space-*`), typography (`--text-*`, `--weight-*`), shadows, timing
- `components.css` — layout, cards, callouts (uses tokens only)
- `animations.css` — keyframes and animation utilities (uses tokens only)

## Naming

- CSS classes: BEM-lite (`section--hook`, `callout callout--use`, `viz-container`)
- Custom properties: lowercase with hyphens (`--color-accent-primary`)

## Adding new values

Define new colors, spacing, or durations in `tokens.css` first, then reference via `var(--*)` everywhere else.

Run the `design-system-audit` skill to find violations.
